    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int getDirectionValue()
      return the flag TYPE_DIRECTION_OUT, TYPE_DIRECTION_IN, TYPE_UNKONW of the gpio direction
      int getPortValue()
      return the value TYPE_VALUE_HIGH,TYPE_VALUE_LOW of gpio port
      void gpio_free()
      free the port you have already hold
      boolean gpio_request()
      when you decide to use a gpio Gpio(int), you should first call this function, and check its return value if return true, means you can use this gpio Gpio(int); if return false, means this gpio Gpio(int) has already be used.
      void setDirectionValue(int flag, int value)
      set the gpio direction as input or output
      void setPortValue(int flag)
      set a flag TYPE_VALUE_HIGH,TYPE_VALUE_LOW to gpio port
